//Image is Square or Round with solid Background (is not transparent) -> Start here!
Choose any Image you want to make into a Profile Picture
Open in GIMP
Make circular selection
Invert selection
Turn selection to Alpha (might be necessary to Bucketfill with black or white and then Select by Color)
Export ~.png

//Image is Round with no Background (is transparent) but not cut to minimal Size -> Start here!
Open ~.png with GIMP
Crop Image to Content
Scale to at least 160x160px or any multitude of that
Export and overwrite ~.png

//Image is Round with no Background (is transparent) and cut to minimal Size -> Start here!
Open in Inkscape
Set Document Size to 160x160px or the multitude of resolution of the Image and set shown UoM to px
Create Circle with Elipse Tool
Set Position to 0,0 and Size to 160,160 or the multitude of resolution of the Image
Turn off Fill
Turn on Stroke (Blue RGBA:00a8e8ff, Stroke Width 4px times the multitude of resulution of the Image)
Scale Image to fit (if necessary due to Circle covering important features)
Center Image
Export at 160x160px as Lastname-160x160.png
